producer.name: CRYOBS-CLIM
producer.title: CRYosphere, an OBServatory of CLIMate
producer.description: CRYOBS-CLIM (CRYosphere, an OBServatory of CLIMate) is based on three existing entities (GLACIOCLIM, CENACLAM and PermaFRANCE) that have been producing exceptional datasets of cryospheric components over a large time period and in different climate regions (temperate, tropical, polar). Fifty three actors including 7 french laboratories as well as international partners are involved.
producer.objectives: Estimate the impacts of cryosphere evolutions on high-altitude, high-latitudes ecosystems and also at regional to global scales (water resources, sea level rise).
producer.measuredVariables: Datasets includes: Glaciological measurements on 12 reference glaciers in different climate regions. Meteorological and hydrological measurements are also conducted on most of the glaciers since at least one decade. Weekly measurements of snowpack properties, daily meteorological and snowpack conditions have been acquired at Col de Porte since 1960. Intensive measurements of snow properties have been collected at the Col du Lac Blanc since 1990.Boundary layer meteorological observations and snowpack properties have been measured at Dome C since 2006. Surface temperature and dynamics of rock glaciers in the French Alps are measured since 2003 and 1982, respectively. Ground temperature of permafrost is measured in high mountain rock walls (especially in the Mont Blanc massif), flat bedrock and a rock glacier since 2009.
